---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebSite",
  "name": "Advocacy-Led Growth",
  "url": "https://advocacyled.com",
  "description": "ALG is a go-to-market motion where existing participants become the primary engine of distribution, trust, and pipeline. The 1:1:N framework.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Roy",
    "url": "https://twitter.com/doubts"
  }
};
---

<Base
  title="Advocacy-Led Growth - The 1:1:N Framework"
  description="People show off. Claim their tribe. Shout what they stand for. Companies create the moments that trigger all three. This pattern can be framed, replicated, and scaled. Let's call it Advocacy-Led Growth."
  activeNav="home"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>

  <div class="section animate-in">

    <h1 class="t-display" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-8); font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5.5vw, 3.4rem); line-height: 1.15;">
      People show off.<br>
      Claim their tribe.<br>
      Shout what they stand for.
    </h1>

    <p class="section-body" style="max-width: 620px; font-size: 1.15rem; margin-bottom: var(--sp-8); line-height: 1.7;">
      Especially after finishing something real - a certification earned, a conference that landed, a first week at a company they believe in.
    </p>

    <p class="section-body" style="max-width: 620px; font-size: 1.15rem; margin-bottom: var(--sp-8); line-height: 1.7;">
      Every company creates these moments. And it's never just one person. Thirty earned that certification. Two hundred walked out of that session. A whole class onboarded the same week.
    </p>

    <p class="section-body" style="max-width: 620px; font-size: 1.15rem; margin-bottom: var(--sp-8); line-height: 1.7;">
      One of them posts on LinkedIn. A colleague sees it, posts theirs. Then another. Suddenly thousands of professionals across their combined networks are seeing the same authentic signal  - from people they actually trust.
    </p>

    <p class="section-body" style="max-width: 620px; font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: var(--sp-8); line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted);">
      This happens after every conference. Every certification cohort. Every onboarding class. The same sequence: moment &rarr; pride &rarr; share &rarr; cascade &rarr; reach.
    </p>

    <p class="section-body" style="max-width: 620px; font-size: 1.15rem; margin-bottom: var(--sp-10); line-height: 1.7;">
      It's a pattern. It can be framed, replicated, and scaled.
    </p>

    <h2 class="t-display" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-4); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4.5vw, 2.8rem);">
      Let's call it<br><em class="t-accent t-italic">Advocacy&#8209;Led Growth.</em>
    </h2>

    <p class="section-body" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);">
      <strong>Roy</strong>, <a href="https://twitter.com/doubts" style="color: var(--accent);">@doubts</a>
    </p>
    <p class="t-label">Coined 2024 &middot; Framework v0.2</p>

  </div>

  <!-- WHO THIS IS FOR -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">
      <span class="num">~</span> Who this is for
    </div>

    <p class="section-body" style="max-width: 620px; font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: var(--sp-6); line-height: 1.7;">
      More content. More ads. More outreach. The playbook is the same everywhere. You've run it. You've optimized it. And you can feel the returns flattening - not because the execution is wrong, but because the model has a ceiling.
    </p>

    <p class="section-body" style="max-width: 620px; font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: var(--sp-4); line-height: 1.7;">
      You're not looking for a better version of what everyone else is running. You're looking for a fundamentally different motion.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- NAVIGATION -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);">
      <span class="num">&rarr;</span> Go deeper
    </div>

    <div class="verticals-grid">
      <a href="/framework" class="vertical-card">
        <span class="vertical-icon">00 framework</span>
        <div class="vertical-name">The 1:1:N Architecture</div>
        <p class="vertical-desc">The complete framework. Distribution architecture, Belief Window, cohort mechanics, signal ecosystem, economics.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/marketing" class="vertical-card">
        <span class="vertical-icon">&rarr; alg/marketing</span>
        <div class="vertical-name">Marketing</div>
        <p class="vertical-desc">Events, product launches, certifications, community campaigns. Every interaction becomes a distribution surface.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/hiring" class="vertical-card">
        <span class="vertical-icon">&rarr; alg/hiring</span>
        <div class="vertical-name">Hiring</div>
        <p class="vertical-desc">Onboarding moments, promotions, team milestones. Your employees' networks are your talent pipeline.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/sales" class="vertical-card">
        <span class="vertical-icon">&rarr; alg/sales</span>
        <div class="vertical-name">Sales</div>
        <p class="vertical-desc">Partner co-selling, customer advocacy, warm introductions. Trust transferred person to person.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/glossary" class="vertical-card">
        <span class="vertical-icon"># reference</span>
        <div class="vertical-name">Glossary</div>
        <p class="vertical-desc">Belief Window, AQL, Cohort Cascade, Signal Ecosystem - the vocabulary of ALG.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/aql" class="vertical-card">
        <span class="vertical-icon"># spec</span>
        <div class="vertical-name">AQL Specification</div>
        <p class="vertical-desc">The Advocacy Qualified Lead - how to measure what ALG produces.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

</Base>
